PBI=games/xscrabble::::xscrabble:::: ::::xscrabble Team::::UNKNOWN::::Unknown-Free::::Graphical::::Games::::game,board,scrabble,puzzle::::feld@FreeBSD.org::::X version of the popular board game ::::To run:<br>Simply type xscrabble. This will bring up the setup box which will allow you to enter the names and displays and other info for the game to wish to play. Then click on the Start Game button, (or Load Previous if you're restarting a game). The main program, xscrab, will then be automatically called with the appropriate options.<br>The game is saved after every turn (in "~/.xscrabble.save" of the person running it) and can be restarted by running xscrabble, entering exactly the same info, and hitting the Load Previous button.<br>This was a student project, and there are not likely to be any future releases.<br>Have fun,<br>Matt Chapman. ::::::::::::::::::::
