PBI=x11/xsel-conrad::::xsel-conrad:::: ::::xsel-conrad Team::::http://www.vergenet.net/~conrad/software/xsel/::::xsel-conrad::::Text::::X11::::x.org,selection::::feld@FreeBSD.org::::Access X selection from command line ::::XSel is a command-line program for getting and setting the contents of the X selection. Normally this is only accessible by manually highlighting information and pasting it with the middle mouse button.<br>This port is similar to x11/xsel, but with different CLI syntax and a bit more functionality. It is a lot more popular, too.<br>WWW: http://www.vergenet.net/~conrad/software/xsel/ ::::::::::::::::::::
