PBI=x11/xsnow::::xsnow:::: ::::xsnow Team::::http://dropmix.xs4all.nl/rick/Xsnow/::::Custom (Free)::::Graphical::::X11::::desktop,background::::feld@FreeBSD.org::::Create a snowy and Santa-y desktop ::::Xsnow displays lovely moving snowflakes on your desktop, with Santa Claus<br>running all over the screen.<br>WWW: http://dropmix.xs4all.nl/rick/Xsnow/ ::::::::::::::::::::
PBI=x11/xterm::::xterm:::: ::::xterm Team::::http://invisible-island.net/xterm/::::Unknown-Free::::Graphical::::X11::::system,terminal::::feld@FreeBSD.org::::Terminal emulator for the X Window System ::::The xterm program is the standard terminal emulator for the X Window System. It provides DEC VT102/VT220 and Tektronix 4014 compatible terminals for programs that can't use the window system directly. If the underlying operating system supports terminal resizing capabilities (for example, the SIGWINCH signal in systems derived from 4.3bsd), xterm will use the facilities to notify programs running in the window whenever it is resized.<br>WWW: http://invisible-island.net/xterm/ ::::::::::::::::::::
PBI=x11/xvkbd::::xvkbd:::: ::::xvkbd Team::::http://homepage3.nifty.com/tsato/xvkbd/::::GPLv2::::Graphical::::X11::::keyboard::::feld@FreeBSD.org::::Virtual keyboard for X applications ::::xvkbd is a virtual (graphical) keyboard program for X Window System which provides facility to enter characters onto other clients (softwares) by clicking on a keyboard displayed on the screen. This may be used for systems without a hardware keyboard such as kiosk terminals or handheld devices. This program also has facility to send characters specified as the command line option to another client.<br>Author: Tom Sato <VEF00200@nifty.ne.jp> WWW: http://homepage3.nifty.com/tsato/xvkbd/ ::::::::::::::::::::
